The '''Jedi Temple detention center''',<ref name="Abyss" /> also known as the '''Temple Detention Center'''<ref name="NoP">''[[Nexus of Power]]''</ref> or '''Sith containment cells''', was a series of secure chambers located in the [[First Knowledge Quarter/Legends|southwest quarter]] of the [[Jedi Temple/Legends|Jedi Temple]] on [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]]. Established millennia before the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]] to house captured [[Sith/Legends|Sith]] and their [[Sithspawn/Legends|creatures]], the Center would later be used to hold insolent members of the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi Order]] from minor to major infractions.<ref name="SWCL" /> While the chambers would be destroyed during the [[Great Jedi Purge/Legends|Great Jedi Purge]] at the rise of the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]], the Center would be reconstructed in the [[New Jedi Temple]] circa [[35 ABY/Legends|35 ABY]].<ref name="LOTFE" />

==History==
Erected in some form shortly after the establishment of the Order's permanent presence on Coruscant, the Detention Center would hold prisoners during the [[Great Sith War/Legends|Great Sith War]] and the [[Jedi Civil War]].<ref name="SWCL" /> While the Detention Center would be abandoned following the [[First Jedi Purge]] of [[3954 BBY]], the Order would reclaim the Temple soon after and hold it for several more centuries.<ref name="Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic II: The Sith Lords">''[[Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic II: The Sith Lords]]''</ref>

The Detention Center again fell to the Sith when the resurgent [[Sith Empire/Legends|Empire]] returned from the [[Unknown Regions/Legends|Unknown Regions]] to [[Sacking of Coruscant|sack the capital]] and oust the Jedi from the Temple. The damage was too extensive to restore immediately, as the [[Galactic Senate/Legends|Galactic Senate]] too overstretched to be able to raise taxes to repair the Temple for several years.<ref name="Timeline 1" /> However, the Temple was eventually rebuilt and the Detention Center was erected anew. After the [[New Sith Wars]] and the supposed extinction of the Sith the Detention Center would come to hold more non-[[Force-sensitive/Legends|Force-sensitive]] prisoners all of which would typically be turned over to the [[Coruscant Security Force/Legends|Coruscant Security Force]] after being debriefed and interrogated.<ref name="SWCL" />

[[File:JediTempleDetentionCenter-Sabotage.png|thumb|left|250px|The detention center during the Clone Wars.]]
During the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]] criminal [[Car Affa/Legends|Car Affa]] was apprehended by [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knight]] [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker]] and brought to the detention center for questioning by the Order's interrogators.<ref name="Lightsaber Lost">{{TCW|Lightsaber Lost}}</ref> At the end of the war in [[19 BBY/Legends|19 BBY]] the last [[Dark Lord of the Sith/Legends|Dark Lord of the Sith]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Darth Sidious]], in his alter ego of [[Supreme Chancellor/Legends|Supreme Chancellor]] Palpatine, ordered the Temple routed of all Jedi by the [[Grand Army of the Republic/Legends|Grand Army of the Republic]]. Led by [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]], the [[501st Legion/Legends|501st Legion]] stormed the complex and carried out Sidious's [[Operation: Knightfall/Legends|orders]] to the letter.<ref name="ROTS" />

The ancient edifice would lay abandoned throughout the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]], falling apart over the decades. After Sidious was killed at the [[Battle of Endor/Legends|Battle of Endor]] and the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] forces were driven from Coruscant, the [[New Jedi Order]] retook the Temple for a time; though the Detention center went unused.<ref name="BRS">''[[Star Wars Battlefront: Renegade Squadron]]''</ref> With the [[Yuuzhan Vong War]], the Temple was damaged beyond repair and left to fall apart.<ref name="The New Jedi Order: Enemy Lines II: Rebel Stand">''[[The New Jedi Order: Enemy Lines II: Rebel Stand]]''</ref>

Following the war the newly formed [[Galactic Federation of Free Alliances|Galactic Alliance's]] [[Chief of State (Galactic Alliance)|Chief of State]] ordered the Temple rebuilt as a gift to the heroic [[New Jedi Order]]. Using blueprints recovered from the old [[Jedi Archives/Legends|Jedi Archives]], the [[Reconstruction Authority]] erected a [[New Jedi Temple|new Temple]] over the old foundations. Restored, the Detention Center would come to house Padawan's that misbehaved at the Temple and [[Dark Jedi/Legends|Dark Jedi]].<ref name="LOTFE" /> Following the [[Dark Nest Crisis]], the Order decided to house rogue Jedi [[Raynar Thul]] here, after he had been severely traumatized during his stay with the [[Killik/Legends|Killiks]]. While healing the young Knight the [[Jedi healer/Legends|Jedi healers]] sealed Thul in the Center's Asylum Block, the collection of rooms designed to house seriously neurologically damaged individuals.<ref name="FOTJO">''[[Fate of the Jedi: Omen]]''</ref>

During the [[Second Galactic Civil War]] in [[41 ABY]], [[Ben Skywalker]] infiltrated the laundry chute in the fourth level training center's changing room on the instruction of Apprentice [[Seha Dorvald]]. Dorvald had told him that she was relaying these instructions from Skywalker's Master, [[Darth Caedus|Jacen Solo]]. Skywalker was hesitant on entering the shaft, as rumor persisted that they were equipped to dump any living beings in the shaft into the Detention Center.<ref name="LOTFE" />

[[43 ABY|Two years later]], the Asylum Block would become home to the Knights who were stricken with an [[Force psychosis|enigmatic madness]]. As more Knights were put in the chambers, Raynar Thul was finally able to reintegrate into the Temple community. Following his capture by the members of [[Darkmeld]], Knight [[Seff Hellin]] was locked away here so as to be studied more carefully by [[Jedi healer/Legends|Chief Healer]] [[Cilghal]]. Shortly after Hellin was secured here, fellow Knights [[Natua Wan]], [[Yaqeel Saav'etu]], and [[Bazel Warv]] were all forced into the Block after going insane. However, they did not stay long as increased pressure on the Order to turn them over to Chief [[Natasi Daala]] forced the Jedi to act. Knight [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa Solo]] kidnapped the insane Jedi without the knowledge of the [[Jedi High Council (New Jedi Order)|Jedi High Council]] and transported them to the [[Jedi Academy (Shedu Maad)|Jedi academy]] in the [[Transitory Mists]].<ref name="FOTJA">''[[Fate of the Jedi: Abyss]]''</ref>

==Layout==
Located in the southwest quarter of the Temple, the Detention Center was a large area established on the level above the [[Room of a Thousand Fountains/Legends|Room of a Thousand Fountains]] and below the [[Halls of Healing]]. Made up of several different specialized facilities and blocks, the Detention Center was a huge complex. The exterior chambers were lit with a harsh orange light and were used to house Sith, Dark Jedi, and their Sithspawn. Designed to withstand the powers of the [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side of the Force]], most of the chamber was reinforced with [[The Force/Legends|Force]] and [[Lightsaber/Legends|lightsaber]] resistant metals as well as being encased in [[Ray shield/Legends|ray shield]] cover.

Less secure rooms, simple holding chambers were built to hold non-Force-sensitives, as well as Jedi apprentices that had broken Temple rules and needed to be held until a ranking Jedi could issue a just punishment. The laundry shafts in the Temple were designed to capture any living beings that entered the chute and deposit them within a holding room in the Center.<ref name="LOTFE" />

The Asylum Block of the Temple Detention Center was a comfortable two-story [[Transparisteel/Legends|transparisteel]] cube located in its own blue-lit atrium, completely encased in a barrier field. The entire structure was surrounded by [[olbio tree]]s which were home to the Force-negating [[Ysalamiri/Legends|ysalamiri]], a feature that cost the Order quite a large sum of [[Galactic Credit Standard/Legends|credits]]. Upon approach, a small golden access point would form in the barrier field, admitting Jedi into the facility after a retinal scan was performed. A path between two rows of olbio trees led to a control room that contained equipment and security controls used to maintain the entire facility. A commissary was located within the block, access to which was attainable only if a patient was escorted by a healer. A turbolift ran the height of the Block, granting access to the second story catwalk. Each of the cells were designed with comfort in mind, aside from the lack of privacy afforded by the transparisteel walls; though the room's [[Refresher/Legends|refreshers]] were located behind a privacy curtain. Equipped with bolted-down flowform seating and [[Hologram/Legends|holograhic]] entertainment centers in the main living area and a small bed in each resting chamber, the cells were more or less apartments whose tenants could not leave. Each room's door was magnetically sealed, making it impervious to any tricks that a Force-impaired captive might employ. Electronic speakers were installed on the catwalk-side of the cells so that anything the patients might say would be broadcast to the healer standing watch.<ref name="FOTJA" />

